text: This square is a Chinese themed heritage site in the middle of the modern skyscrapers of the city. Many restaurants, cafes, bars, and murals on walls

Amazing place, no matter what time of day.
Plenty of options for scenery, food, drinks and activities.
Car park up and downwards ramp is narrow. Bigger cars may have an issue navigating the car park
Many Drink joints for Happy hours after a hard day at work. Its crowded in the evening.  Good to chill out for the evening.

Visited far east square on Saturday for lunch and loved the place for its vibes. It has lot of cafes and some interesting graffiti. The building architecture is largely restored with colourful windows.
